description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locum Consultant in Palliative Medicine, 6 Months Contract&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7 PAs plus 1:6 2nd on-call &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity for a Locum Consultant in Palliative Medicine has arisen to join our medical team, working along side three other consultants, one of whom is on maternity leave.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;St Wilfrid’s is an established and well supported hospice with 14 in-patient beds, a community service and Living Well Centre, education and bereavement services. The hospice re-located to a purpose-built site in Bosham in 2019.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are keen to develop our services and in particular wish to promote out-patient and Living Well Services in our much larger purpose-built facilities. We also wish to enhance our services for people with chronic heart and lung disease and dementia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will be advertising a replacement Medical Director / Consultant post in early 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are required to be on the GMC’s Specialist Register with a licence to practice or within two months of their expected date of receipt of a CCT at the time of interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our committed team, the working atmosphere is friendly, inspiring and supportive. We offer a comprehensive benefits package which includes holiday entitlement starting at 27 days per year, increasing to 33 days, plus bank holidays, or a continuation of NHS entitlement. A contributory pension scheme, or continuation in the NHS Superannuation Scheme, life assurance, discounted gym membership plus a contributory cash reimbursement plan for you and family members.&lt;/p&gt;
